                <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.01/192: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-06T20:00:00+00:00"
                            >January 6, 1919—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>174. [From Lansing.] Please refer to note from French Ambassador at Washington to
                    Secretary of State dated November 26th, 1918 saying that the French Government
                    has been asked by the Polish National Committee for recognition as <hi
                        rend="italic">de facto</hi> government in regard to: (1) foreign
                    representation; (2) political direction of the Polish army; (3) civil protection
                    of Poles abroad. The French Ambassador says his Government believes request
                    justified, and is inclined to grant desired recognition suggesting further that
                    Allied Governments come to agreement on this point. Last paragraph requests
                    early expression of opinion from Secretary of State. Please transmit by
                    telegraph complete text of reply made by the Department to the French
                    Ambassador’s note. Lansing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
